cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT

The paper discusses the computational power of neural network architectures for natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper specifically focuses on recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and gated recurrent units (GRUs). 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of RNNs and GRUs for natural language processing tasks. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the computational power of neural networks, which is a fundamental topic in machine learning and AI. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the computational power of RNNs and GRUs in terms of their ability to process and generate sequences of symbols, which is a topic related to information theory.
